-- Indexes rise on optimism over profits
-- 
-- Fri Apr 20, 2007 4:33pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/20/us-stocks-indexes-idUSPER07381920070420

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - U.S. stocks jumped on Friday, with the Dow closing at a record high after approaching 13,000, as Google Inc. and Caterpillar Inc. joined the list of companies reporting stronger-than-expected quarterly results. 

 The Dow Jones industrial average was up 154.33 points, or 1.20 percent, at 12,962.96. The Standard & Poor's 500 Index was up 13.70 points, or 0.93 percent, at 1,484.43. The Nasdaq Composite Index was up 21.04 points, or 0.84 percent, at 2,526.39. For the week, the Dow rose 2.8 percent, the S&P gained 2.2 percent and Nasdaq rose 1.4 percent.